<TITLE> Largest Eid congregation expected in Sholakia </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kishoreganj, Dec 20 (bdnews24.com)The country's largest Eid-ul-Azha congregation will take place at Sholakia in Kishoreganj, starting at 9:15am Friday. The local administration and the Eidgah committee have completed preparations for the smooth conduct of the 181st congregation at the same venue. As in the past, it is expected that it will be the largest Eid congregation in the country. Khatib maulana Abul Khair Mohammed Saifullah of the local Bara Bazaar Jamia Mosque is to lead the congregation. As per tradition, three shotgun rounds are to be fired five minutes before the beginning of prayers to draw the attention of the large numbers of people to the congregation. Three minutes later, another two rounds are to be fired and finally one round before the congregation gets underway. Muniruzzaman Khan Chowdhury Sohel, publicity secretary of Sholakia Eidgah Committee, told bdnews24.com: "All steps have been taken to ensure upkeep of the Eidgah, improve the sanitation system and ensure security for the jamaat. Established in 1828, on nearly seven acres of land, the Eidgah was reported to have had 1.25 lakh people in its first congregation. bdnews24.com/corr
